<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id56c53611-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02" identifier="/us/usc/t14/s2511"><num value="2511">§ 2511.</num><heading> Investigations of flag officers and Senior Executive Service employees</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">In conducting an investigation into an allegation of misconduct by a flag officer or member of the Senior Executive Service serving in the Coast Guard, the Inspector General of the Department of Homeland Security shall—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id56c53612-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02" identifier="/us/usc/t14/s2511/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> conduct the investigation in a manner consistent with Department of Defense policies for such an investigation; and</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id56c53613-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02" identifier="/us/usc/t14/s2511/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> consult with the Inspector General of the Department of Defense.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="id56c53614-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02">(Added <ref href="/us/pl/114/120/tII/s220/a">Pub. L. 114–120, title II, § 220(a)</ref>, <date date="2016-02-08">Feb. 8, 2016</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/130/48">130 Stat. 48</ref>, § 430; renumbered § 2511, <ref href="/us/pl/115/282/tI/s114/b">Pub. L. 115–282, title I, § 114(b)</ref>, <date date="2018-12-04">Dec. 4, 2018</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/132/4223">132 Stat. 4223</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
